%% Diagram: Custom 6-step ProxySQL cutover used to move 130 hot tables off mysql1
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant App as Rails app
    participant PXA as ProxySQL (cluster_a)
    participant PXB as ProxySQL (cluster_b)
    participant A as cluster_a primary (source)
    participant B as cluster_b primary (destination)

    Note over A,B: Steady state: B replicates from A; PXB routes to A
    App->>PXA: writes
    PXA->>A: forward writes
    A->>B: standard MySQL replication

    Note over App,B: Cutover script begins (executes in tens of milliseconds)

    PXA->>A: 1. SET GLOBAL read_only=ON
    A-->>PXA: writes now blocked (handful of 5xx)
    PXA->>A: 2. read last executed GTID
    A-->>PXA: GTID = X
    PXB->>B: 3. poll until GTID X arrived
    B-->>PXB: GTID X applied
    PXB->>B: 4. STOP REPLICA from cluster_a
    PXB->>PXB: 5. swap routing target to cluster_b primary
    PXA->>A: 6. SET GLOBAL read_only=OFF (both primaries)
    PXB->>B: 6. SET GLOBAL read_only=OFF

    Note over App,B: Steady state: writes now land on cluster_b primary
    App->>PXB: writes
    PXB->>B: forward writes
